title: BREAKING: Juvenile shot, wounded in West Palm Beach
content:
A male was to taken St. Mary’s Medical Center with injuries that are not believed to life-threatening, said Detective Lori Colombino, spokeswoman for West Palm Beach police.
The shooting happened just after 6:30 p.m. in the 600 block of 47th Street, said Detective Lori Colombino.
Detectives are trying to locate witnesses. Anyone with information is asked to call Detective Ron Robbins at 561-822-1900, or Crime Stoppers of Palm Beach County at 800-458-TIPS (8477).
